What was the main Allied beachhead in southern France during World War II?assistant
115.generation: The main Allied beachhead in southern France during World War II was the one established at the port city of Toulon, which, along with the nearby city of Marseille, served as a significant entry point for the Allies, providing a vital link to the interior of the country, and a crucial stepping stone for the eventual liberation of the rest of France.
